<p>IMMEDIATE SECRET</p>

<p>The United Kingdom Ambassador at Moscow [1] reports that at 7 p.m.</p>

<p>today, M. Molotov summoned him and the United States Ambassador [2] in order to tell them at 5 oâ€™clock he had sent for the Japanese Ambassador [3] and had told him that from tomorrow, 9th August, the Soviet Union would consider itself at war with Japan.</p>

<p>_</p>

<p>1 Sir Archibald Clark Kerr.</p>

<p>2 W. Averell Harriman.</p>

<p>3 Naotake Sato.</p>

